title: 2021 Central Region wrestling: Wrestleback semifinal results (Reg. 5 & 6)
body: 2021 NJSIAA Central Region Wrestling Championships - SaturdayThe best high school boys wrestlers in New Jersey open pursuit of state titles on Saturday with the opening round of the NJSIAA/Rothman Orthopaedics wrestling tournament.The Central Jersey Region tournament is set for Hunterdon Central High School.Complete results are on the way from , so stay tuned.The results for the wrestleback semifinals:13-, Matawan p. 2-, Middlesex, 4:43.5-, Ocean Township md. 6-, Jackson Liberty, 9-1.3-, Christian Brothers d. 5-, Freehold Borough, 8-2.4-, St. John Vianney d. 11-, St. Joseph (Met.), 7-0.3-, Christian Brothers d. 5-, Piscataway, 7-0.11-, Jackson Memorial d. 4-, Howell, 9-2.3-, Howell p. 4-, Middletown South, 5:25.6-, Red Bank Regional d. 5-, Jackson Memorial, 8-6 (SV).3-, Robbinsville d. 4-, Wall, 10-5.5-, Brick Memorial d. 10-, Middletown South, 6-0.1-, Hunterdon Central d. 2-, Spotswood, 13-9.6-, Middletown South d. 8-, Brick Memorial, 7-1.3-, Point Pleasant Beach p. 9-, Middletown South, 1:03.6-, Wall p. 13-, Ocean Township, 4:35.Note to readers: if you purchase something through one of our affiliate links we may earn a commission.
